HEADWORD: Star-spangled
<hw>Star"-span`gled</hw> <pr>(st⟦aum⟧r"-sp⟦acr⟧⟦nsm⟧`g'ld)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <def>Spangled or studded with stars.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Star-spangled banner</b></col>, <cd>the popular name for
the national ensign of the United States; also the name of a poem, the
words of which were composed by Francis Scott Key, which was adopted as
the national anthem of the United States.</cd> <au>F. S.
Key.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Star stereogram</ent>⟦br⟧
